FillerComponent.ManufacturerOrSourceName: XG Sciences Inc., Lansing, MI, USA

Drying-Evaporation.Description: In order to prevent possible hydrolytic scission of the matrix during processing, PLA was preventively dried overnight under vacuum at 90 °C.
In order to prevent possible hydrolytic scission of the matrix during processing, GnP was preventively dried overnight under vacuum at 110 °C.

TwinScrewExtrusion.Extruder: co-rotating twin-screw extruder (type EBV 19/35 D, OMC, Saronno, Italy)

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Before each step, the materials were dried overnight under vacuum at 90 °C, in order to prevent phenomena of hydrolytic chain scission.

Cooling.Description: The molten material coming out from the extruder die was cooled in air and afterwards pelletized to be used for further characterizations.

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.EquipmentUsed: Quanta 200 ESEM, FEI, Hillsboro, OR, USA

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Equipment: Perkin Elmer DSC 7, Waltham, MA, USA
Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Description: Thermal properties of the processed materials were studied using a differential scanning calorimeter (Perkin Elmer DSC 7, Waltham, MA, USA). The experiments were performed under N2 gas flow (20 mL/min).
Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.CycleInformation: Samples underwent a heating/cooling/heating program in the temperature range 30–200 °C. The heating rate was 10 °C/min and the cooling rate was 40 °C/min. The experiments were performed in triplicate.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Equipment: RIGAKU model: D-MAX 25600 HK, Rigaku, Tokyo, Japan
XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: Diffraction patterns were obtained in the 2θ range from 10° to 50° with a sampling width of 0.004° and a scan speed of 4°/min, using Cu Kα  radiation (λ = 1.54 Å).

Raman_Spectroscopy.Equipment: Renishaw InVia Raman Microscope spectrometer equipped with a 532 nm Nd:YAG laser excitation
Raman_Spectroscopy.Description: Measurements were carried out in the range 3000-500 cm-1 with a spectral resolution of 0.5 cm-1.

Rheometery.Description: The rheological characterization was performed using a plate-plate rotational rheometer (HAAKE MARS, Thermo Scientific, Waltham, MA, USA), operating at 190 °C on samples obtained by compression molding as above described. The instrument has been set to operate in the frequency sweep mode in the range 0.1–500 rad/s with a strain of 5%. Before testing, the samples were dried overnight under vacuum at 90 °C. The tests were performed in triplicate.
